(69, 1, '2013-03-25 00:52:36', '2013-03-25 00:52:36', '<h3 style="margin-bottom: 30px;">Cuesko - the Quantity surveying team that is client and project focused, delivering proactive and practical cost solutions to ''drive informed decisions''</h3>\r\n<div style="margin-top: -21px;"> Cuesko (pronounced Q-S-Co) was formed in 2013 by three former Senior Executives of an International <strong>Quantity Surveying Consultancy</strong> operating nationally throughout New Zealand.</div>\r\nThe Directors have a combined 44 years of New Zealand based <em>quantity surveying</em> experience in both commercial and civil construction industries, backed up with international knowledge gained\r\nworking for first tier contractor organisations and professional consultants throughout the world, Cuesko has the skills and experience to add to any project.\r\n<h4>mission statement</h4>\r\n<div class="bulleted">\r\n\r\nA new venture with a new approach….. Cuesko are committed to providing the necessary information that will enable our Clients to make informed decisions and put into effect proper commercial strategies.\r\n\r\nOur aim is to establish long term relationships with our quantity surveying Clients, through a focused, and detailed approach to project delivery alongside an understanding and recognition of our Clients “Big Picture” desired outcome. Repeat business will be a key performance indicator for the success of our consultancy.\r\n\r\nWe will be proactive in our approach and advice, providing risk recognition and practical cost solutions to support our Clients desired outcome in terms of budget, timelines, quality and the aesthetics of a project.\r\n\r\nAs an independent cost consultant we will act independently, and challenge where appropriate, but this will be done as a fully integrated member of the consultant team. A consultant team that acts as a team will better function in the interests of the Client and the project.\r\n\r\n“Cause and Effect” will be our guideline for demonstrating to the client and his consultant team what the outcome of decisions and changes really mean.\r\n\r\n“No Surprises” will be our guideline for forecasting the outturn cost of projects. We will achieve this through comprehensive cost reporting techniques based on the lessons learnt from 44 years of NZ based quantity surveying experience, and our in depth knowledge of international project delivery operations and procedures.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'About Us', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-quantity-surveying', '', '', '2014-11-07 03:58:10', '2014-11-07 03:58:10', '', 0, 'http://localhost/cuesko.co.nz/?page_id=69', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(71, 1, '2013-03-25 00:52:52', '2013-03-25 00:52:52', '<h1>Quantity Surveyor - ‘Whole of Project’ Quantity Surveying Services</h1>\r\nCuesko provides a full range of quantity surveying services tailored to clients’ needs. Our four  Directors individually and collectively provide a wealth of experience in leading hand-picked teams to define and deliver vastly improved construction outcomes for clients.\r\n\r\nWhen you work with Cuesko as your quantity surveyor – you’re gaining the expertise in quantity  surveying services that you need to drive more informed decisions. Our people have delivered expert pre-contract and post-contract cost management services on some of New Zealand’s most  significant construction projects.\r\n\r\nDepending on your project and requirements we will tailor our team and our quantity surveying services to ensure you have the best possible information to inform your best possible outcome  - whether that’s stepping you through every stage of construction or simply supporting a specific  need.\r\n\r\nExamples of our quantity surveying services are listed below. With Cuesko you will always have the  detail, the responsiveness and the ‘big picture’ thinking that reliably delivers superior outcomes.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/cuesko.co.nz/contact-us/">Start the conversation today.</a>\r\n\r\n[one_half]\r\n<div class="info-title" style="color: #582a40; text-shadow: 1px 1px 1px #ffffff; font-size: 24px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 25px;">pre-contract services</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cost Estimation at all stages of a Project from concept through to pre tender.</li>\r\n	<li>Feasibility Studies.</li>\r\n	<li>Estimate Peer Reviews.</li>\r\n	<li>Parallel Estimates.</li>\r\n	<li>TOC Validations.</li>\r\n	<li>Procurement and Contract Advice.</li>\r\n	<li>Tender Documentation.</li>\r\n	<li>Tender Evaluation/ Analysis.</li>\r\n	<li>Value Engineering.</li>\r\n	<li>Precondition Certification for Funders.</li>\r\n	<li>Lifecycle, Capex and Opex calculations</li>\r\n	<li>Expert cost advice</li>\r\n	<li>Comparative cost analysis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<div class="info-title" style="color: #582a40; text-shadow: 1px 1px 1px #ffffff; font-size: 24px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 25px;">post-contract services</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Contract Administration under NZS3910 or NZS3915 and other standard forms of contract including NEC3, FIDIC etc...\r\nComprehensive Financial Reporting</li>\r\n	<li>Stakeholder Cost Allocations.</li>\r\n	<li>Payment Recommendations</li>\r\n	<li>Cost to Complete / Outturn Cost Forecasts</li>\r\n	<li>Project Cashflows</li>\r\n	<li>Cost Audits</li>\r\n	<li>Processing, Evaluation and Recommendations on Variations, Extension of Time Claims, Delay and Disruption Costs, Acceleration Costs etc. under different forms of Contract.</li>\r\n	<li>Financial Progress Certifications for Funders.</li>\r\n	<li>Commercial Advice.</li>\r\n	<li>Contractual Advice.</li>\r\n	<li>Sustainability Cost Advice</li>\r\n	<li>Expert Statements / Witness</li>\r\n	<li>Depreciation Schedules</li>\r\n	<li>Asset Allocations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/one_half_last]', 'Services', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'quantity-surveying-services', '', '', '2014-10-25 01:02:41', '2014-10-25 01:02:41', '', 0, 'http://localhost/cuesko.co.nz/?page_id=71', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(73, 1, '2013-03-25 00:53:08', '2013-03-25 00:53:08', '<div style="height: 150px; margin-left: -15px; margin-top: -67px; margin-bottom: 55px; overflow: hidden; z-index: 0; width: 976px;">\r\n<div style="margin-top: -21px;"><img src="http://localhost/cuesko.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/who1.png" alt="Who we are" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\nCuesko as a new venture brings enthusiasm to do things better, with a new approach and attitude to construction cost management. Cuesko is Client and Project focused delivering proactive and practical cost solutions to “Drive informed decisions.”\r\n\r\nWe are independent in our approach to allow us to question design and engineering proposals. However we also function as a fully integrated member of the consultant team to ensure that the project team work as a unit to get the best commercial outcome.\r\n\r\nWith a combined 44 years of New Zealand based experience in both commercial and civil construction industries, backed up with International knowledge gained working for first tier Contractor Organisations and Professional Consultants throughout the world, Cuesko has the skills and experience to add value to any Project.\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding-bottom: 15px;"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-95" src="http://localhost/cuesko.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/bio_02.png" alt="bio_02" width="117" height="148" /></td>\r\n<td style="padding-top: 50px;" valign="top"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-98" src="http://localhost/cuesko.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/icon.png" alt="icon" width="11" height="12" /></td>\r\n<td style="padding-top: 50px; width: 175px;" valign="top">John Giles\r\nDirectorCommercial Cost\r\nSpecialist</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n<td style="padding-bottom: 15px;"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-96" src="http://localhost/cuesko.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/bio_04.png" alt="bio_04" width="117" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td style="padding-top: 50px;" valign="top"><img class="alignleft size-f